Former head of the foreign desk at the State Security Agency Mo Shaik will continue his testimony at the state capture inquiry. JOHANNESBURG - Former head of the foreign desk at the State Security Agency, Mo Shaik will continue his testimony at the state capture inquiry. Shaik said that Gupta family was already a threat to national security by 2010. READ: Guptas could have been stopped: Mo Shaik He told the commission the Waterkloof scandal might never have happened if an investigation he and his colleagues wanted had taken place three years earlier.